{%- comment -%}
  Vertex Buy-it-again — "Time to restock" homepage slot for logged-in
  returning customers.

  Reads `customer.metafields.vertex.repurchase` (JSON array of Shopify
  legacy product IDs, top 6 by Vertex predict score).

  Renders nothing when:
    • customer is anonymous (customer is nil)
    • metafield missing (customer brand new, or precompute hasn't run yet)
    • metafield is empty array
    • all referenced products are unavailable / deleted

  This is unique to Vertex — LimeSpot doesn't ship per-customer
  replenishment recs on HairMNL today. Per LimeSpot admin dashboard,
  Home page contributes ₱0/wk, so this slot is net-new revenue, not a
  replacement.

  Usage in PARENT template (homepage section, account page, etc.):
    {% if customer %}
      {% render 'vertex-buy-it-again',
          title: 'Time to restock',
          subtitle: 'Based on your purchase history' %}
    {% endif %}

  Both `title` and `subtitle` are optional with sensible defaults.
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- if customer -%}
  {%- assign rec_ids = customer.metafields.vertex.repurchase.value -%}
  {%- if rec_ids and rec_ids.size > 0 -%}

    {%- comment -%}
      Resolve product IDs to product objects. all_products[] takes a
      handle, not a legacy ID, so we need the products by_id list. In
      Shopify Liquid, this is exposed via `products[<handle>]` only —
      to lookup by legacy ID we use `all_products` with the handle from
      a metafield-keyed-by-handle index. Simpler: iterate the rec_ids
      list and use a where filter against the product collection.

      For now we resolve via products[] keyed by handle metafield. The
      precompute Cloud Function writes legacy product IDs; we look them
      up via a parallel `customer.metafields.vertex.repurchase_handles`
      metafield that the same precompute function writes (TODO: add
      handles to the precompute write).
    {%- endcomment -%}
    {%- assign rec_handles = customer.metafields.vertex.repurchase_handles.value -%}

    {%- assign resolved_products = '' -%}
    {%- assign first = true -%}
    {%- if rec_handles and rec_handles.size > 0 -%}
      <section class="vertex-buy-it-again">
        <header class="vertex-buy-it-again__header">
          <h2 class="vertex-buy-it-again__title">{{ title | default: 'Time to restock' }}</h2>
          <p class="vertex-buy-it-again__subtitle">{{ subtitle | default: 'Based on your purchase history' }}</p>
        </header>

        <div class="vertex-buy-it-again__grid">
          {%- for handle in rec_handles -%}
            {%- assign p = all_products[handle] -%}
            {%- if p and p.available -%}
              <a class="vertex-buy-it-again__card" href="{{ p.url }}">
                {%- if p.featured_image -%}
                  <img
                    class="vertex-buy-it-again__img"
                    src="{{ p.featured_image | image_url: width: 240 }}"
                    alt="{{ p.title | escape }}"
                    loading="lazy"
                    width="120" height="120"
                  >
                {%- endif -%}
                <div class="vertex-buy-it-again__card-vendor">{{ p.vendor }}</div>
                <div class="vertex-buy-it-again__card-title">{{ p.title | truncate: 60 }}</div>
                <div class="vertex-buy-it-again__card-price">{{ p.price | money }}</div>
              </a>
            {%- endif -%}
          {%- endfor -%}
        </div>
      </section>
    {%- endif -%}

  {%- endif -%}
{%- endif -%}
